&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Deployed Customer Engineer (DCE)&lt;/strong&gt;, you are the technical bridge between Couchbase’s engineering excellence and our customers’ most ambitious business goals. You are an embedded technical partner who writes production-grade code, builds high-performance database architectures, and ensures our platform powers the heart of mission-critical, AI-driven applications. You will deliver strategic solutioning and work within customer engineering teams to deliver business outcomes through technical implementations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unlike traditional engineers or solutions architects, the DCE operates at the intersection of:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Software Engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Systems Architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer Success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product Feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The DCE is responsible for accelerating customer outcomes by:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building real-world implementations and pilot solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solving complex technical challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translating customer needs into scalable solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acting as a bridge between customers and internal product/engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Technical Implementation &amp;amp; Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hands-on Coding:&lt;/strong&gt; Write clean, scalable code to build integrations, APIs, and data models that connect Couchbase with customer ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Configuration:&lt;/strong&gt; Expertly configure Couchbase Server, Capella (DBaaS), and Mobile products to optimize for latency, throughput, and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architecture Design:&lt;/strong&gt; Design and implement advanced data architectures, including &lt;strong&gt;Vector Search&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)&lt;/strong&gt; patterns for modern AI applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
